RABIES, WEEKLY REPORT - FRANCE, INDONESIA, USA
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Sat, 18 Oct 1997 16:38:55 -0300
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Media reports

(1) France - Rabies Free
A news report from Paris today says that France, for the first time in 29
years, reported no cases of rabies for a 12-month period.
(2) Indonesia - Outbreak
A report in the Jakarta Post on Thu, 16 Oct says that authorities will
catch and destroy about 14,000 stray dogs and vaccinate 6000 pets in order
to control an outbreak of rabies in the Ciamis district in western Java.
[The dog is considered an "impure" animal in predominantly Muslim Indonesia.]

(3) USA - Cases
The Hartford Courant (Connecticut) reported Fri 17 Oct that a rabid skunk
in the town of Plainville bit a woman who stopped on a road to help what
she thought was an injured cat.
The Portland Press Herald (Washington) reported Fri 17 Oct a rabid raccoon
found in the town of Topsham near an elementary school.
The Kansas City Star (Missouri) reported Thu, 16 Oct a rabid bat in an
industrial part of the section of Liberty, making it the third rabid bat
found in sections south of the Missouri river in recent months.
The Columbus Dispatch (Ohio) reported Wed, 15 Oct a rabid bat found by
children on the grounds of an elementary school in Madison Mills on 10 Oct.
--
Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
